{"key":"processedPost-9645245","value":{"id":9645245,"first":9644146,"last":9655240,"when":1232476685,"utime":"01/20/09 08:38 PM","content":"They crack in the cool down phase if the PC cools off too fast.&nbsp; AA pressure cookers aren't quite as bad about it as others, because their thickness allows for a slightly slower cool down.&nbsp;  At the end of the cycle, try reducing your stove to its lowest setting, rather than off.&nbsp; After half an hour or so, shut it off.&nbsp; Remember, the pressure inside your jars is also 15 psi, so if the PC itself loses pressure faster than the jars do, they'll break.&nbsp; Mason jars are designed to hold vacuum, but not pressure.<br />RR","title":"Re: why did my jars crack?"}}